values:
I haven't been on here in forever!!  It's crazy!  But I been reading some entries from the few friends that kept me on your list.


How is everyone!!??

Super super super busy!  I'm hoping to update one night this week, but not sure when!  Lots of pics to share.  

Hope everyone's doing good.

We had an excellent time.  I must say, I got pretty drunk and it was fun.  Kids played in the pool and on the swing set all day!  We ate good bbq that Tj prepared, it was sooooo good!  He had it marinating for 3 days.  Mmmmmm.  We decided we better be safe and not drive to the fireworks cause we were all drinking margaritas all day.  So we did some little ones of our own.  The kids still enjoyed it, plus I had sparklers and glow bracelets for them.  It was us, a few of our neighbors, and my friend that just moved down here, her mom, and two kids.  We had a lovely time.  I'm glad we hung out with some more neighbors.  It was funny cause they were saying it was cool to have social people in the neighborhood finally.  We were like, I know!  We been meeting people all year long, but no one socializes a lot.  So now we have a little clique, lol.  The couple is having their first baby and she is just miserable, lol.  She is terrified too, so I am sure she will be asking me a lot.  She already said she is gonna use me for drop in care when I have room.  

But anyways, imma go search the internet or something.

So we got up, headed to the Y to sign up.  Can't wait to start going.  Then we decided to hit up a few rummage sales.  We had some great buys actually.  We got a picture frame, Jorden a Thomas the Train rug, 2 candles sets, some walkie talkie's for the kids, a sushi kit, a dog igloo house, and a couch!  We got an $80 sectional cream leather couch!  It is awesome find!  Our couches have gotten extremely uncomfortable, you can feel every spring, and everything.  They still look ok, but they are uncomfortable, so I am gonna see what I can get for them on Craigslist.  I am so excited for our new couch, it looks good in our living room!  And I can't believe they only wanted $100 and we talked him into $80!  They were an elderly couple, beautiful clean house, that just wanted to buy a new couch!  The pull out couch needs a new pad, and the recliner is wobly, but other than that, it's in good condition!  I'd say we had a great day rummaging!

SIMS 3 is GREAT!!

A few things I am not a fan of... the people are not as pretty, they actually look kinda weird!  But the multiple possibilities for them are awesome.  

Also, I can't figure out how to have more than 1 family in the same neighborhood, it makes me make a whole new game.  Huh, imma do some more research on it...

When you force something on someone that they don't want, they will never fully commit.


Think about that....tell your thoughts, do you agree?

I am just exhausted this week.  Ugh, really, just lazy!  I just wanna play sims all day, lol. 

I drastically changed my diet because I realized I should probably loose 20 pounds this month to make my goal in July.  So, yogurt and fruit for breakfast.  Nothing but fruit and nuts for snack.  At the end of the week though, I'll have a sweet.  Probably keep it home made cake or muffin or something like that.  Nothing but salad for lunch and dinner.  I am allowing myself to put meat on my salad at dinner time as long as it is baked.  Or even a taco salad every now and again.  I'm prolly gonna add in brown rice once I see a significant amount of weight come off.  Drinking nothing but water daily.  Should be able to get to the grocery store tomorrow evening, we need to go, but are running extremely low on fruit.  I am hoping they have good of everything too so I can get a variety.  I really want some pineapples, haven't seen those yet.

I wish these kids would sleep so I can take a short SIM break, lol.

I started a lovely bet with a friend of mine and her cousin which puts me at loosing 42.8 pounds by July 3rd.  I have motivation and stamina, but it seems like a lot to think about, lol.  We started last week and this week I lost a healthy 2 pounds.  Probably more, but cause I'm on my lovely period, my water weight is high.  I've been working out all week and "dieting."  I have been doing a mix of the Fat Smash Diet, with just portion sizing.  Seems to be working ok.  In the end, if I win, they both by me an outfit, and vice versa.  It will be nice.  I keep thinking positively.  

I should have a new girl starting on Monday, a 3year old.  That should be fun.  Jorden is surrounded by girls all day, lol.  He is every bit boy though.  Super hero to the fullest.  It's so cute.  He even has Jaylynn knowing the Superheroes.  We were watching something during dinner and I am like who is that, Jay goes, "That's Aquaman, I know that cause I'm a smart girl."  Lol, they crack me up.  Jorden started telling me about all them, and I got lost, lol.  

Well, my contacts are hurting, so gonna go take those out and maybe see what movies are on HBO, or catch up on my shows.

I haven't been on here in ages, well 5 weeks I guess, but it seems longer.  So, I have been doing ok.  We have had some woohaas and woonoooos that past few weeks.  Our vacations went well.  Vegas was awesome!  If you are on my Myspace or Facebook, you should have seen pics already.  Wisconsin was fun, didn't get to do much or see as many people as I wanted, but still, it was fun.  Good to see my sisters and mom again.  My baby is 3!!  I can't believe it.  We should be on our next kid already!!  Why is it taking so long!!  Well, we will continue to pray, and try of course.  Daycare business is going ok.  I just unexpectedly lost a kid this week so that sucks because we just got a new car!  Oh yeah, my Mitsu puked on me, engine completely died!  Over $2500 to fix, and with it already having close to 200k miles on it, we thought it was not worth it.  So we got a 2008 Hyundai Senata.  We have our first new car!!  Well, it was preowned, but not for long, has 32k for miles.  So now we are stuck with a car note.  Oh, well, it was much needed.  I LOVE the car.  

Tj and I have been doing good, working everything out still.  I believe we will stand the test of time though.  Marriage is good when you learn to trust and believe in it.  I am happy with the decisions I have made last year and this year, and now am looking towards the future.  

Jaylynn graduates pre-k in 3 weeks!  Can't wait, they are having a little ceremony and everything.  I am contemplating taking that day off from daycare so that I can go and not have any worries of bringing kids with me, or missing it because I have too many kids, we will see.  I know I'm taking off the first day of kindergarten, lol.  

Wedding business is going ok, finally starting to get my name out there more after my first wedding of the year a couple weekends ago.  Ugh, I have an idea for my blog though, that may help some more.  Gotta get some interviews with vendors lined up.  Tj has got the works for his catering business going.  We even have a dance studio wanting to use him as their personal caterer when they have events with them.  So that could work out great!!  Gotta start getting business cards made up and stuff.  So we are definitely keeping busy trying to get out businesses out there in this dang recession!!  

Blu and Sammie's puppy's are gorgeous!!  She had 7 of them.  I'll have to post a pic up.  We are taking one of them.  They should be ready this weekend, so yay to new puppy training!!  Haha, already bought disinfectant cleaner for all the accidents we are sure to have.  We are thinking of naming him Taz.  I have definitely turned into a dog lover and are getting better at owning them, lol.  Blu is trained very well, and we are proud of that.  

School, is school, still working at it, should be done I think June of next year now since I took a two week break a couple weeks ago.  I gotta stop that, lol.  

Alright, Imma catch up on everyone's journals since kids are still napping!
got it on with the neighbors dog weeks ago, and we think she is preggo.  Puppies may be on the way.... as well as his neuter appointment!

So, I go to call Tj to tell him to bring some dinner home and my phone keeps telling me that my phone can not be recognized??  So I'm confused.  I check my account online, all paid up.  I try to text, not working.  So I *2 to Sprint and I get the activation line??  WTF?? I have had the same phone for 3 or 4 years now, why do I need to activate.  So I start, it gets me to a person, I ask her what's going on?  She asks if I got a new phone?? No!  I told her I have been looking to upgrade since I have $175 for having the same phone for years.  So I tell her, you know my husband may be at the store right now getting me a new phone, could that be why?? And she is like, oh no, I don't want to tell you, sorry to tell you this, but your phone is now connected to the Palm Centro!!  Ha!!  Yes!!  When he gets home, I will have a new phone!! Lol, she starts laughing and said sorry to ruin my surprise!!  Lol!  She goes congratulations on your new phone!!  Too cute.  I knew there were reasons why I love him!!

Man was I ready for the weekend.  Daycare has completely taken over, lol.  But I do keep a good schedule and the days are not that long.  But, by the end, I just wanna serve dinner and relax.  I barely made it down to my computer this week because I have just been chillen on the couch!  Tj had a decent check this week, so we got to pay more bills than we thought!  Yay!!  Lol.  And I got half of next weeks pay early since they will be with mom this weekend until Tuesday evening.  She will pay me the other half on Monday.  I will be mailing my packet in next week after I get my finger printing done, finally.  They are only open between 9-4, so I have been putting it off since that means Tj has to stay with the kids for a hour or so.  But, I need to get it in because then I can add more kids, and receive the food program benefits, which is extra money coming in to pay for food and stuff for the kids.  

I cleaned majorly after the kids left to make sure I had a relaxing weekend!  I blasted my ipod on the living room speakers and went to work, sweeping everywhere, scrubbing, dusting, wiping down the toys, and washing the kitchen up.  I picked up the bathrooms, but did not sanitize them yet.  I even did my bedroom.  I got all the laundry lined up to start tomorrow, and I want to clean my refrigerator, I have noticed some spills in there that have been getting on my nerves.  

Anyway, Jay and Jor are up watching Ice Age 2, probably fell asleep by now, and I am gonna get some homework done, and then hit up the Sims until Tj gets home.
Ugh, I feel so much better to be back online!!  My world has been lost all week long!!  Lol.  I'll be back on tonight to update.

F(^& SH** C%9* WH($&*!!!!!!!!!!!!

I hate my DVR box right now.  It self deleted ALL my Grey's Anatomy's for space.  It couldn't delete just the older ones, but ALL!!  I suppose it's my fault for not having it set on only erase when I do it....... but shit, it should have known I was waiting for a long cold night and a bag of popcorn to catch up!!!  Now I gotta sit in front of the computer and do it!!!  UGH!!!!

Well, I found one computer place that backs up, so I don't have to worry about my pictures.  Yay.  

I attempted to have some fun and play sims before my computer is out of commission, but it just kept shutting down and restarting.  I did manage to build a house and half way design it before it shut down for the 3rd time.  I finally gave up just now.  I go on Tj's lap top to do some homework and the classroom is still shut down for maintenance.  They usually do these over night, not the whole day.  It is supposed to be back running tomorrow morning.  Ugh.  I have participation to get done.  But, I won't have late points because I have a ticket number from tech support.  But still, it's annoying.  

So, I guess imma go fiddle around on myspace.

I am backing up my pictures before I take my computer in on Monday because I am not sure if they will do it.  I don't like photobucket quality.  And I already used my Flickr account max.  Does anyone know of another good website to upload too??  I have all my new ones from my digital camera to save from the last year.  It's more than 1gb because they won't fit back on my memory card.  So, I need a new site.  Otherwise I'll have to make another flickr account.

First week of my daycare almost done.  I have been watching 1 3 year old all day, and his sister when she comes home from school.  She goes to school with Jaylynn, so Tj picks her up.  Tj's best friend and his family have been here visiting all week before he had to leave back for Iraq today.  : (  I have been watching their kids too, 5 and 3.  So it has been like 4 kids all day, and 6 kids in the afternoon, lol.  I got used to it really quick!!  I enjoy the little boy, but his older sister, I could do with out.  Let's just say lack of discipline, she acts like she is deaf, she's lazy (I have to make her put her own shoes on and she is about to turn 5), and you can clearly tell she has been bribed with food for the first 3 years.  Poor girl.  The 3 year old boy, although he's very small, I think he was a preemie cause he is like Jorden's size who is only about to turn 3 and this little boy will be 4 this year, but anyway, he is very smart, although he has listening issues, not as bad as his sister, and his attention span is a lot longer as well.  

But enough ranting.  I need to look up some more activities to plan my next few weeks.  I forget how short attention spans are at the toddler age and when I was thinking 30 minutes for an activity, I am getting 15-20.  So I need to revamp, lol.  They love going outside though, of course, what kid doesn't.  But man it has been cold.  Yesterday we only lasted 15 minutes before they were all complaining.  

I like the idea of actually having money coming in every week!!  This is awesome, lol.  Granted it's only $90, but hey man, that is cool!  Hopefully I should have some more kids soon.  

Well, they are all napping, I cleaned the kitchen while they were eating lunch, and now I am gonna do some homework while I have chance. 


BTW, my computer is completely taken over by the virus.  It changed my background to black with flashing red note that says I have a virus and need to take action.  I can't push control alt delete anymore, it says the administrator turned that off!!  I am gonna bring it somewhere tonight or tomorrow depending on where it is.  Hopefully they can save my hard drive.  Abra, my friend who's daughter did it, offered to pay for the fix.  Thank GOD she is very nice and understandable that her daughter did it, and she will fix it.  


Oh, before I go, Blu's punk self may have gotten his girlfriend, our lovely neighbor's dog pregnant!!  I hope not!!!  We caught them in the middle of the action yesterday and tried to get them apart and they were stuck!!!! UGH!!!!  They said she was on her last few days of her heat.  Ugh, I knew we should have gotten him neutered a long time ago!!  I hope she is not pregnant.

Got back earlier from a weekend in Alabama and Mississippi.  Funeral for Tj's great grandmother, and went to see his father give his first sermon in church.  We enjoyed ourselves.  Tell you about that later.  Before I left, I shut my computer off, which is not something I ever do, it is always running.  But anyway, it is louder than Blu barking right now, lol.  I opened it up and it's one of my fans.  I cleaned off the caked on dirt, but it is still loud, I believe it is dieing.  Hopefully I can take it in to replace it as soon as this week.  

Finished my final statistics class!!  YES!!  And I should be getting an A!!  I start a new class tomorrow.  Also tomorrow I have 2 kids to watch!!  Yay!!  Risa's Tiny Tots is starting!! Alright, now I'm gonna head upstairs before my computer drives me bananas!!

I came back from my walk a bit ago, did push ups, did 10 minute ab video, took a shower, and now I wanna lay back down, but I hear Jorden in the bathroom.  Darn, if only he was sleeping for another half hour, lol.

Ever since I posted my link to my website on Craigslist I have been getting emails and calls after calls after calls.  It is pretty cool.  I have already interviewed with 3 different parents, all wanting to start next week.  So we will see if anyone actually signs up.  I have another interview on Saturday.  I need to get my rooms set up.  I have been waiting to see what ages I have, that will determine what and how many of each toy I would need.  I need to go buy a small table.  At my CPR class on Saturday, I met with a lady that was a teacher, and she said she has tons of stuff and she found a daycare in the area that is closing, so she will let me know when they are selling all the stuff, so I can go.  That is cool, but I hope they aren't too pricy, because our monetary situation doesn't really have room for extras.  I have some things, and definately enough activities to keep everyone occupied, I think my room will look better to parents though when I have it fully set up.  Anyway, this is going great, and I am glad I decided to do this!!

Finally, a potentionally successful at home business!!

(Wedding planning is great, when I have weddings!!  Lol, I actually do have one in April, and I am doing centerpieces and florals for another in September.)

...for the people in my household and anyone that visits.  I have contracted viruses, and now have pop ups every time I click on something!  

UGH!!  I have scanned, rescanned, deleted, rescanned, cleaned, restarted, all that.  Now I am waiting for Tj to get home so he can take off my McAfee stuff and re put it on.  We think the virus got in there because I keep having pop ups no matter what I clean off.  UGH!!!!!  

If it is NOT your computer, don't down load anything.  That's all.
Hey guys, here is a started version of my website for my daycare. Tell me what you think. I have a logo too, just haven't added it and other pictures on the site yet. Risa's Tiny Tots

So, how was everyone's Christmas??  Ours was wonderful.  We ate a huge breakfast, opened gifts, played with gifts, had a huge dinner, and then just lounged around all day.  It was great, just the 4 of us in the house again.  I can not wait until my friend moves out, it will feel like home again and the kids will be back on schedule, and everything.  It will be nice. 
Kids got a bunch of stuff, Tj and I got a few things as well.  My favorite have to be my exercise stuff I got.  I got a ball and weights from my sister.  And with a gift card we got, I picked up a slimmer belt and a sauna suit to wear around the house and while I am exercising.  I have been really good on my diet and will get fully back on it starting tomorrow.  Christmas got me a little out of wack, lol.  I will be exercising full steam again, and hopefully should be shedding pounds left and right, lol!!  I already lost close to 15lbs just fom dieting, so when I start working out, I will be going hard core!!  (And I managed not to gain any weight last week!  Yay!  But anyway, I'm gonna go see if dinner is done.   
 
Reddick Christmas 2008
Jaylynn Opening Her First Gift




Jorden Opening His First Gift

His Favorite Gift: The dinosaur that moves and roars!

Jaylynn's Favorite Gift: She loves to paint!

The both got new bikes, but Jorden's old school Radio Flyer was the big hit!!
Merry Christmas!!

Happy birthday to me, happy birthday to me, happy birthday dear me, happy birthday to me!!!



I am officially quarter of a century years old.  OMG!

news.yahoo.com/s/ap/18th_baby


This is so beautiful!!  I wish that could be me someday!!
OMG, I'm gonna be quarter of a century on Monday!!  Man, I am getting old!

So I started hemraging (spelling), bleeding 1 pad an hour yesterday, went into the Er again, and by the end, I ended up getting a D & C.  All the bleeding and clotting I was doing did nothing because the sac was still there.  I am recovering now at home, having a horrible head reaction to the anesthesia they gave, but I am drugged up and I feel it coming on, lol.  So I am gonna lay down now.

I am thinking of getting a yorkie terrier.  

And we will continue to try again for another baby after this passes.  I chose to do it naturally, unless they need to intervene and get everything out later.  I actually had a much better experience at the ER than last time, so I felt better, and they actually advised to me that a DNC, or whatver it is, can scar the uteris, so the doctor advised that I pass it naturally, and come back for a follow up to make sure everything is clear.  


Ugh... I really was expecting a baby in 6-7 months.

"Little girls know being the princess, the queen and then the bride.  

All boys know is to be the superhero."



This quote struck my attention.  My cousin sent me some notes from a show, on the book, "How To Love a Black Man."  It sounds interesting, but generalizing sometimes doesn't fit the mold.

01. What's the last TV show you saw?
Sweet 16, ugh, it made me sick.  

02. What are you wearing at the moment?
Black work out pants, a turquoise tank top, and a black zip up hoodie.  

03. Have you lost any friends recently? Why?
No

04. What is your favorite scent?
Irish Spring soap. 

05. What is your favorite drink?
Koolaid

06. What do you drink the most?
Koolaid

07. What is your favorite restaurant?
Olive Garden

08. What will you be doing after finishing this?
Going to get my car tested at emissions.  

09. What did you want to be when you grew up?
A super star!

10. Your favorite romantic movie?
The Little Mermaid

11. What kind of person do you think the person who tagged you is?
I think she is a young person at heart, and is trying hard at her life, but probably needs some help to get where she wants to be, and could use some breaks.

The dark and zombies.  

13. What's your favorite item of clothing?
My black zip up hoodie I am wearing right now.

Usually never before midnight.

I can not get my mind on this paper that is due today.  I just do not get it.  And I really don't want points taken off for turning it in tomorrow, I just don't get it!!!  I read and did research, but have not written one single sentence!  ERRR.

So Desperate Housewives, if you haven't watched the show yet, I'm gonna ruin some of it, so don't read.

I am pissed about Susan and Mike.  WTF!!! After all they been through, all that I cried over in the past seasons, all that, and they break up!!!!  I am definately pissed about that.  Bree not having the baby!!  WTF!!  That was just rude.  But Bree is definately a biotch to Catherine, and I can see this blowing up in her face later.  Gabby and her fat kids, poor kids.  I hope that fixes.  And are Lynette's twins super ugly or what!!  What happened to her other 2 kids?? I hope they don't disappear into tv land, lol.  What about Edie's new hubby, psycho!!  Who do you think he's after??  I am thinking Mike or Orson....but I'm not sure just yet.  

Brothers & Sisters, love this show.  I am mad a Sarah though, she has such a big mouth, and always had.  Tommy is such a downer all the time too, he is never happy, and I can't believe he fired Kevin.  I felt so bad for Kevin.  I think Sarah may be getting fired in the future as well.... but we shall see.  

You know after all my shows just came back on, I feel like part of my life is back, lol!!  It's a great feeling.  I pretty much sat and watched those and then watched Sex & the City movie yesterday, which was great!  The kids were playing right on the porch off the living room, so it was great, lol.  

Oh, and then when Tj got home we watched Heroes, lol, so it was a tv day, all day. Filled with great shows.

Did anyone else watch the season opening of family guy and was not that impressed with it?  I wanted to see more of Peter, lol.  He's hilarious.  I mean, there was some funny parts, but not many.  

I just finished homework, not ready to start the new week though, 1 individual paper, and 1 team paper due, ugh.

I'm gonna go lay down and watch Desperate Housewives and Brothers & Sisters that I recorded last night!  Woohoo!  And prolly take a nap with Jorden after that.

You can not put slideshows up on the info page, because I just tried, and it wiped out everything I had underneath them, suck.  I tried pressing back to at least copy all my html I had, and it was gone.  Oh well.  I'll have to redo that, but now I am annoyed from sitting here and doing these slideshows for the past hour.  Took long because I had to upload some pictures to photobucket.  Ugh.  Hopefully they post here, so I can show off my lovely kids.  Pictures from birth on.     


**EDIT**  Appartently I can't put them here either.  WTF??  It's just html, does lj not support slide shows?  I don't feel like looking up the answer right now either, ugh.  I am super annoyed now.  I'm gonna go wake Jorden up and play with the kids.

Have you guys seen this? 

Push Up Challenge

I am starting it tomorrow!  Eek!  Lol.  I'm in column 3 because I can do 22 push ups consecutively, thank you!  It sounds interesting and something new to my work out routine.  Which has been going excellent by the way!  Tj and I go to the gym daily, accept Sundays.


I have been working a lot on school work and wedding work lately.  Trying to get things scheduled and in a routine for both things.  I convinced myself to start an event blog about my ideas, experiences, and such with weddings and different events.  I have come up with some good entries, but have not posted them yet.  Will get that started once I have at least one to two weeks of ideas ready.  I want to post as often as I can.     

Alright, I'm heading to cook dinner.  Tacos for the kids, taco salad for me!  Yummy.  Catching up on friends tonight!

Today was a good day.  We found out we do not qualify for any state aid, so that sucks.  But at the same time, the car is now fixed!  Yay!  Now we just need to save some money off his next check for the plates and we won't be riding dirty anymore!  At least I won't, lol.  Tj still gotta get his license taken care of.  I had a good work out at the gym this morning.  Turkey sandwich for lunch, salad with porkchop for dinner (which was really yummy, Tj is really a great cook), made a no-bake cheese cake, which was Kroger brand and it was delicious!  We did some small grocery shopping like always.  I was the mystery reader at Jaylynn's school, which was fun and she loved it!  Oh, and I started my classes back today online.  Not so great cause my 2 week break was feeling good, but knowledge is always good.  I will be done in 2010!  That seems so far away, lol!  


I am contemplating getting rid of all my custom content on my sims game and redoing my neighborhood that I have been playing since I got the game, years ago......... Not sure if I really wanna do it though!  I got generations built up!

Maybe it's the upset stomach night I had all night.

Maybe the aches and pains in my back.

Maybe the dread of returning to class work tomorrow.  (And the teacher has not posted the syllabus yet, so no early reading for me, ugh.)

Maybe it's the gloomy day.

All I know is, I do not want to go to the gym, but I must. 

I guess I will head there now.  Errrr.



I need to post this somewhere to refer back too, pay no attention.

This Week
Business Stuff

Fix my Vendor Page on my website

Look up and email a few vendors and set meetings to meet with them soon

House Stuff

Clean Jorden's Room
Put Jorden's Laundry Away
Do Jaylynn's Laundry
Do Tj's Laundry
Do my flower arrangements for the living room
Clean Office
Get rid of junk pile in Garage
Call guy to cut grass
